node.text:
The First Cliff Walk in Switzerland wraps around the mountains of Grindelwald and is a breathtaking experience for those brave enough to embark on the hike up the Bernese Alps. This walkway is situated at 2,168 meters above sea level (7,112 ft). Would you go explore this region with 300 kilometres (187 miles) of hiking trails? ⁣
⁣
📌Grindelwald, Switzerland 🇨🇭⁣
⁣
📸 Thank you @michelphotographych for your great video!⁣
⁣
⁣✅ If you want to be featured too, don't forget to follow @hikingtheglobe and tag # hikingtheglobe in your photos. Cheers!⁣
⁣

Greenland is wonderfully beautiful and has a wild and raw nature that you will not experience elsewhere. Icebergs, northern lights, midnight sun, ice sheets, green fields, rugged cliffs, an exciting wildlife and even beautiful sandy beaches are among the things you will experience in the Greenlandic nature.⁣
⁣
📌 Greenland 🇬🇱⁣

node.text:
Being in Japan not always means the enthusiastic and fun loving city of Tokyo, temples, and monasteries, which Japan is usually perceived as. It also means the mountains and the peace that we get therein. Japan has around 70% of its land mountainous. There are around 18000 mountains in Japan as recorded recently and many of them are ready to give you the thrill and the peace at the same time. Japanese people are very fond of their mountains and so will be any hiker visiting the place.⁣
⁣
📌 Japan 🇯🇵⁣
⁣
📸 Thank you @koichi1717 @danielkordan @88mercury @t_tetsuji @aish_jayamaha @risephoto0263 and @washima12 for your awesome photos!

The Azores is an autonomous region of Portugal comprising nine volcanic islands in the North Atlantic  899 miles (1,446 km) west of Lisbon, Portugal. The dramatic landscapes and the pristine nature of the Azores are simply breathtaking. The Azores have 80+ trails officially, making it a great hiking destination. The trails are well maintained with clear signage at the starting points and markers during the trail, perfect also for self-guided Azores hiking tours.⁣
⁣
📌 The Azores, Portugal 🇵🇹⁣
⁣
📸 Thank you @deliorodrigues @brunoazera and @johan_drone_adventures for your awesome photos!⁣

Home to an extensive collection of historical and cultural attractions, Vietnam is undoubtedly one of the most fascinating countries in Southeast Asia. The country’s landscapes offer hikers a unique experience. This is where you can hike along terraced rice paddies, underneath towering limestone mountain ranges and into the largest cave in the world.⁣
⁣
📌 Vietnam 🇻🇳 ⁣

📸 Thank you @ninjarod @smashpop @imduhy @oli.langevin @thomaschuphoto @chad_gerber and @komm_rum_travel for your awesome photos!⁣

A glance at a topo map of Turkey reveals that this is a country of mountains. Rising from all four directions, mountains encircle the peninsula of Anatolia. A part of the Alpine-Himalayan orogenic belt, Turkey has mountainous regions with different geological formations. These magnificent mountains and forests are mostly undeveloped, existing as wonderful natural preserves for an extraordinary variety of fauna and flora.⁣
⁣
📸 Thank you @bahadirsansarci @ilhan1077 @erdiyilmaz83 @tansutopuzoglu and @erol3937 for your great captures!⁣

node.text:
When discussing about traveling and hiking in Europe, Czech Republic usually doesn’t come up as an outdoor destination. Mountains there are not very high compared to the neighboring countries, but there are several great options for hiking that can take you to amazing rock formations, to mountain trails following the Polish border, to majestic castles, to deep canyons and to peaceful pine forests.⁣
⁣
📌 The Czech Republic 🇨🇿⁣
⁣
📸 Thank you @tom_juenemann @ericfriese @tomashavel @mrs._pegy @bokehm0n and @filipmanhal for your awesome photos!⁣
